text.tspan: I'm a hacker commited to the values of the software freedom movement.
Skills: IT training & education, libre software development and advocacy, pcb design,
digital electronics, reverse engineering, device driver development, digital fabrication,
open standards, public speaking, graphic design.
Hardware Engineering at Musical Operating Devices

flowRoot.flowPara: Hardware engineering for the MOD Duo project
<https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/modduo/mod-duo-the-limitless-multi-effects-pedal>
Main attributions:
* Schematic design with Eeschema (KiCAD)
* PCB layout with pcbnew (KiCAD)
* Iterative PCB prototyping at the company's electronics lab (proof-of-concepts / validation of Release Candidate hardware revisions)
* Embedded Linux device driver development (ALSA System on Chip drivers)
* Daily Open Hardware contributions to the project files on GitHub (https://github.com/portalmod/)
We're a 3D printing business focused on popularizing rapid prototyping machines in Brazil. We're fully commited to free software and open hardware design.
* Company's lead role in R&D
* Hardware design and software/firmware development for an open hardware 3D printer (Metamáquina 2)
* Regular contributions to upstream free software projects such as OpenSCAD and Repetier-Firmware.
* Management of the Metamáquina 2 production line.

* Lecturer in several educational workshops covering topics such as 3D modelling, 3D printers maintainence and operation, free software development tools, hacker ethics and open innovation. Workshops also included guided assembly and educational exploration of DIY hardware kits such as the SpokePOV and the Uzebox 8-bit video-game, reverse engineering techniques and learning by tinkering in general.
* Tutorship at extra-curricular STEM classes at the Saint Paul's british school in São Paulo, Brazil.

text.tspan: Libre Software development at Metapolator - Design Fonts and Families Faster

flowRoot.flowPara: Software development for the Metapolator project, a web application that helps
type designers working on parametric type design.
* Import and Export routines supporting the Zipped UFO file format.
* OpenType.js integration to also handle the OTF file format.
Further project info at:
* https://github.com/metapolator
* http://metapolator.com/
